descript.abstract: Boundaries of Historic Property and District Designations in North Carolina (not including archaeological sites): National Register of Historic Places (NR) listings, Study List (SL) entries for potential nomination to the National Register, and Determinations of Eligibility (DOE) under Section 106 of the National Historic Preservation Act of 1966, as amended.
descript.purpose: Show the boundaries of historic properties and districts in North Carolina designated under federal and state historic preservation programs for which it is possible to delineate an official boundary. For local landmark and district designations, see the Local Designations datasets. For undesignated properties recorded in historic property field surveys, see the Surveyed Only datasets.
descript.supplinf: Polygons delineate boundaries of designated properties and districts where it is possible to draw the official NR or DOE boundary or the suggested SL boundary. Many designated sites do not have officially defined boundaries. Thus while every designated property is represented by a point, only a subset of those designations have associated boundaries. See the points feature class for more complete coverage of all designations.

idinfo.useconst: Users are advised that data is amended by the HPO on a daily basis, and shapefiles extracted on a fixed date are quickly outdated. Contact the HPO for details about web mapping services that display current data.
idinfo.datacred: State Historic Preservation Office, Office of Archives and History, North Carolina Department of Cultural Resources
idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.1.3500

dataqual.logic: Official boundaries for designated properties and districts are usually based on land surveys, tax parcels, natural or man-made features such as streams, ridge lines, roads, or fence lines, or a combination of such sources. Boundaries are drawn in ArcMap by capturing tax parcels and/or tracing such features from orthophotography or map backgrounds.
dataqual.complete: Though National Register points are complete and vetted as of publication date, boundaries are drawn only for those NR listings for which there are clearly defined and delineated boundaries in the nomination documents, approximately 75% of the total. Many early nominations did not have clearly defined boundaries. Determined Eligible boundaries, when drawn, are based on maps in environmental assessment reports that are accepted by the HPO and consulting agencies party to the reports. Study List boundaries are by definition "for study," and thus tentative. Relatively few SL and DOE entries have boundaries drawn.

altsys.altenc: Explicit elevation coordinate included with horizontal coordinates

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.
